Redis - "Remote Dictionary Service"

-  small-ish quantity of data that doesn't need the relational structure that Postgres offers, and requires fast access

-  session data in a dynamic web interface

- a cache for some Postgres data which is going to be accessed very often (ie: load it when a user logs in)

- Counting things (INCRBY operation)

Postgres

- complex lookups

